# Documentation Updates Rule

## Purpose

This rule defines the process for updating GlyphNova documentation when features are added, modified, or completed. It ensures consistent documentation across README.md, implementation status reports, and feature tracking documents.

## When to Update Documentation

Update documentation when:
- A new feature is implemented
- An existing feature is modified or enhanced
- A feature status changes (pending ‚Üí in progress ‚Üí complete)
- New limitations or issues are discovered
- Screenshots are added for new features
- A new plan file is created

